Authentication and Authorization

# 

<span key="3935b9c639174c9987a5dbc1c223e051"><span offset-key="3935b9c639174c9987a5dbc1c223e051:0">Authentication and Authorization</span></span>

## 

<span key="8187196bb319428fb7c69a3841ab3211"><span offset-key="8187196bb319428fb7c69a3841ab3211:0">Authentication vs. Authorization</span></span>

<span key="d657e82466d8412ca2bcf576153d927f">**Authentication**<span offset-key="d657e82466d8412ca2bcf576153d927f:1"> is when we provide our user credentials to a login form. Typically in modern auth flows, you give a username and password, and your API will verify that you are who you say you are based on your credentials provided. This step verifies users in your system.</span></span>

<span key="18abd7c86dd945998c9e2cb3f99dd05e">**Authorization**<span offset-key="18abd7c86dd945998c9e2cb3f99dd05e:1"> is when you grant access/permissions to portions of your website to individuals who've previously been authenticated. This usually requires some form of user management.</span></span>

<span key="c8e636d657d14066a31877c2cec0e561"><span offset-key="c8e636d657d14066a31877c2cec0e561:0">In this module, we'll go over how we approach both authentication and authorization in Labs using Okta.</span></span>

<span key="bcc6bf1ebd294c4a93c54c215cdccdd6"><span offset-key="bcc6bf1ebd294c4a93c54c215cdccdd6:0"><span slate-zero-width="n">â€‹</span></span></span>

# 

<span key="217c4417dd02404e9644083d51b5e356"><span offset-key="217c4417dd02404e9644083d51b5e356:0">Okta</span></span>

## 

<span key="c150a4a6addb4da881dd0798fb3e1f3f">**What is Okta?**</span>

<span key="1329a96e5c3e4467b66368aa9970c848"><span offset-key="1329a96e5c3e4467b66368aa9970c848:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://www.okta.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c728c946dada4dd9a3aaee3454f91065" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-1773_259-1774-237__"><span data-key="de08c2ca6ad44c10ba63ff2e7e6463d7"><span data-offset-key="de08c2ca6ad44c10ba63ff2e7e6463d7:0">Okta (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="ece8596379314f05a4067111035d0424"><span offset-key="ece8596379314f05a4067111035d0424:0"> is an identity management service that's used in Labs to provide centralized authentication for Labs applications.</span></span>

<span key="6b59bbb1b22c4a498a53ada0ac14a005"><span offset-key="6b59bbb1b22c4a498a53ada0ac14a005:0">We use a centralized identity management service because it's typically the way applications are authenticated in the industry. This gives you practice using centralized identity management technologies like </span></span><a href="https://developer.okta.com/blog/2017/06/21/what-the-heck-is-oauth" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="4e14eeef7b7644db8ec4ef6f4d0b2425" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-1773_259-1774-237__"><span data-key="bc41aece70684fdabab7596338161ab0"><span data-offset-key="bc41aece70684fdabab7596338161ab0:0">OAuth (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="4f23fdd9e5d04d0eaa206964cd8822b6"><span offset-key="4f23fdd9e5d04d0eaa206964cd8822b6:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://openid.net/connect/faq/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="7c3d76dbf8fe4569b9a617b4729a70f1" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-1773_259-1774-237__"><span data-key="3abe21f557194cfbb5ec7c998c01b427"><span data-offset-key="3abe21f557194cfbb5ec7c998c01b427:0">OIDC (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="e0a5d98740904b019399e6e6ef69c78a"><span offset-key="e0a5d98740904b019399e6e6ef69c78a:0">.</span></span>

<span key="120e80ac10ec42c3bb26079ab427ab9b"><span offset-key="120e80ac10ec42c3bb26079ab427ab9b:0">We use Okta specifically because it's an </span></span><a href="https://www.okta.com/resources/access-management-leader-gartner-magic-quadrant" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="7a16bf4f82b04338b7d6a590bcd22a1e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-1773_259-1774-237__"><span data-key="8a3d91ed02c14a53a598fab5471a60ce"><span data-offset-key="8a3d91ed02c14a53a598fab5471a60ce:0">industry leader (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="b12ccf3a100547188691709ffac048b1"><span offset-key="b12ccf3a100547188691709ffac048b1:0"> and has high-quality support and documentation.</span></span>

<span key="9d91ffaffa074240815814363bdff842"><span offset-key="9d91ffaffa074240815814363bdff842:0">The Okta Account</span></span>

<span key="78cc974c28f14d13a0ecb2f2865e351f"><span offset-key="78cc974c28f14d13a0ecb2f2865e351f:0">Okta provides centralized identity management. This means that you can have a single set of identities that can be used across many different applications. If you use Google services, you can see this in action as you log in to Google once but can move between Google apps (Mail, Calendar, Sheets, etc.) without having to log in each time.We use Okta the same way. There is a single Labs Okta account that has a set of identities that can access all Labs applications. These identities are test users that can be used by teams for testing their applications without having to constantly create new identities.Since Labs applications are always under development, it's very handy to have a set of test identities readily available to test various aspects of your application.Labs applications should always authenticate using the alias (auth.lambdalabs.dev), though, for reference, the Labs Organization URL is: </span></span><a href="https://dev-625244.okta.comdashboard" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c09feb281133449191f96aaf81067b8c" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-1773_259-1774-237__"><span data-key="f4c748b9fc864afa9db5aed80607cdb6"><span data-offset-key="f4c748b9fc864afa9db5aed80607cdb6:0">https://dev-625244.okta.com</span></span></span></a><span key="0c43a7fccea2467a98b2d627a91dfce8"><span offset-key="0c43a7fccea2467a98b2d627a91dfce8:0">â€‹</span></span>

# 

<span key="e6dd0ccdae324132b6224a67e6878eec"><span offset-key="e6dd0ccdae324132b6224a67e6878eec:0">Administrative Tasks</span></span>

<span key="d1e13e2d5221472cb7ce6443a87a9048"><span offset-key="d1e13e2d5221472cb7ce6443a87a9048:0">The following are administrative tasks that you'll need to perform in Okta to support Labs teams.</span></span>

## 

<span key="b64afc85e06948a0afd1368f41e15ea3"><span offset-key="b64afc85e06948a0afd1368f41e15ea3:0">Retrieve Product Client ID</span></span>

<span key="0ff1f84a021945988ddd8c54216d871d"><span offset-key="0ff1f84a021945988ddd8c54216d871d:0">There is a single Client ID for each product that must be supplied to Labs project teams in order for them to enable authentication. Each product will be set up as an Okta Application. The Client ID can be found using the Admin interface, by clicking on the Applications Tab.Products have one client id that is shared among all active projects working on that product. Client IDs should not be shared across products.</span></span>

## 

<span key="36fdeae65fad4696b85e7021b5607c51"><span offset-key="36fdeae65fad4696b85e7021b5607c51:0">Issuer URI</span></span>
